.Dd May 11, 2026
.Dt NOBODY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm nobody
.Nd run agents without ambient authority
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm run
.Op Fl p Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar command
.Op Ar argument ...
.Nm
.Cm policy check
.Op Ar policy
.Nm
.Cm policy simulate
.Op Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar action
.Op Ar argument ...
.Nm
.Cm trace show
.Op Fl -jsonl
.Op Ar latest | file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a least-privilege execution runtime for AI agents and other autonomous
software.
It reads a TOML policy, evaluates capability decisions, filters the child
environment, prepares the strongest available filesystem sandbox, runs the
permitted command, and appends structured JSONL trace events.
.Pp
The current runtime enforces process policy and environment filtering on every
platform.
On Linux it also uses Landlock to enforce filesystem read and write grants when
the policy can be represented as granted path trees.
On non-Linux hosts, filesystem policy is diagnostic only and
.Nm
prints a warning before spawning the command.
.Pp
Network, MCP, browser-control, and secret-broker enforcement are planned but are
not implemented in this milestone.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Xo
.Cm run
.Op Fl p Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar command
.Op Ar argument ...
.Xc
Run
.Ar command
under
.Ar policy .
The default policy path is
.Pa nobody.toml .
If the requested process is denied, the command is not spawned.
.It Cm policy check Op Ar policy
Parse
.Ar policy
and report the trace path that would be used.
The default policy path is
.Pa nobody.toml .
.It Xo
.Cm policy simulate
.Op Ar policy
.Fl -
.Ar action
.Op Ar argument ...
.Xc
Evaluate a single policy action without running a command.
Supported action forms are:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "net.connect host:port" -compact
.It Cm process.exec Ar program Op Ar argument ...
.It Cm env.read Ar name
.It Cm fs.read Ar path
.It Cm fs.write Ar path
.It Cm net.connect Ar host:port
.El
.It Xo
.Cm trace show
.Op Fl -jsonl
.Op Ar latest | file
.Xc
Read trace events.
The default target is
.Cm latest ,
which reads
.Pa .nobody/runs/latest.jsonl
and shows only the last run in that append-only file.
With
.Fl -jsonl ,
print selected events as newline-delimited JSON instead of the compact terminal
view.
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl p , Fl -policy Ar file
Read policy from
.Ar file .
Used by
.Cm run .
.It Fl -jsonl
Print trace events as JSONL.
Used by
.Cm trace show .
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Show command help.
.It Fl V , Fl -version
Show the program version.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Nm
does not require special environment variables.
.Pp
The parent environment is evaluated against the policy's
.Va env
table before the child process starts.
If
.Va env.clear
is true, the child receives only variables that match
.Va env.allow
and do not match
.Va env.deny .
If
.Va env.clear
is false, variables are inherited unless denied.
.Pp
.Ev PATH
controls normal operating-system command lookup for the child process.
.Ev HOME
is used when policy matching compares
.Pa ~/...
patterns with expanded home-directory paths.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa nobody.toml
Default policy file.
.It Pa .nobody/runs/latest.jsonl
Default append-only trace file.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It 0
The command or inspection operation completed successfully.
.It Ar n
.Cm run
exits with the child command's non-zero exit status when the command starts and
then fails.
.It 1
The policy could not be read, policy evaluation denied the requested process,
the trace could not be read, sandbox preparation failed, or the child terminated
without an ordinary exit code.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal
nobody run -- echo hello
nobody run --policy nobody.toml -- echo hello
nobody policy check nobody.toml
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- fs.read .env
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- fs.write README.md
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- process.exec curl
nobody policy simulate nobody.toml -- net.connect github.com:443
nobody trace show latest
nobody trace show latest --jsonl
.Ed
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Common diagnostics include:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Qq invalid TOML policy
The policy file parsed as invalid TOML or used an unknown field.
.It Qq process denied by policy
The requested command matched
.Va process.deny
or did not match a non-empty
.Va process.allow .
.It Qq trace is empty
.Cm trace show
read a trace file with no events.
.It Qq Landlock filesystem enforcement is only available on Linux
The host selected the diagnostic no-op sandbox backend.
.It Qq cannot enforce fs.deny
Linux Landlock cannot express a deny carve-out below an already-granted path.
Grant narrower read/write paths instead.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
